  "verdict": "POSITIVE-STRUCTURAL-DRIFT",
  "verdict_text": "Strict-strong-form pro-system functoriality at the cochain-morphism level FAILS bit-exactly. The degree-3 residual on (e_2,e_3) palindromes drifts from +/- 1/(3*2^16) at n_max=2 to +/- 1/2^16 at n_max=3 (factor of -3), then is BIT-EXACT FIXED at -1/2^16 for n_max=4 -- identifying the n_max>=3 value as the structural pro-limit, with n_max=2 the boundary transient. The pull-back P^*_{3->2}[phi_4^(3)] does NOT equal phi_4^(2): the increment delta(B phi_4) = -1/(3*2^14) closes the (b phi_2^(2) + B phi_4^(2)) residual to (b phi_2^(3) + B phi_4^(3)) bit-exactly (1/196608 + (-1/49152) = -1/65536). CM-eta has the same structural pattern: drifts from -59/(3*2^18) at n_max=2 to +/- 1/2^13 at n_max>=3, bit-exact fixed. Both cocycle towers exhibit strict-strong-form failure on commutative algebra A; CM-eta is not the cochain-clean alternative at degree 3. Empirical confirmation of the Connes 1994 / Loday published-open gap on entire-cyclic functoriality.",
